<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6a2f647-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s30502"><num value="30502">§ 30502.</num><heading> Application</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6a2f648-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s30502/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">In General</inline>.—</heading><content>Except as otherwise provided, this chapter (except section 30521) applies to seagoing vessels and vessels used on lakes or rivers or in inland navigation, including canal boats, barges, and lighters.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6a2f649-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s30502/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Exception</inline>.—</heading><content>This chapter (except for section 30526) shall not apply to covered small passenger vessels.</content>
</subsection>
